spent
in the country, would be of
infinite
service
to her. Vieurville was ordered to
send
a carriage at nine, and it being the
last
morning
of my novitiate, I
desired
not be
disturbed
till
it was time for me to enter the chapel. This
request
I knew would be complied with, as it
would be
supposed
, I
wished
