I returned to my lodgings, with a heart
considerably
lightened, and was
desired
to call
on the Earl again in about ten days, when he
should
have had time to
consult
what was
best
to
be done. On the appointed morning I repaired
to the Earl, I found him
seated
at a table writing,
a letter lay unfolded before him.
Dorcas,
said
he, (
rising
and leading me to a
seat
) I have received letters from England
since
I
saw
you.
Do they mention me, my Lord?
Yes, they
say
you have long led a very
dissolute
life, and that you have eloped from your
husband
with a young officer, and taken with you a
quantity of money and jewels.
Heaven forgive them,
said
I, and
burst
