?
Time, my Lord, perhaps may inform you with
my
reasons
for acting thus. At
present
I cannot
alledge the true
cause
, and will never
stoop
to a
mean equivocation to
excuse
an action, which I
am
sensible
is perfectly right.
The Earl was piqued, he bowed and left the
cottage.
Lydia,
said
Dorcas, if you love your mother,
you will avoid the Earl of Landaff.
He is generous and humane,
said
Lydia,
Trust
not to appearances, replied her mother,
when you
shall
learn a tale which I could tell you,
you will then, like me, tremble at the name of
Renfew.
Peace, with the
speed
of a courier, now fled
from the
