, led
her through a
suit
of
superb
apartments and told
her; if
she
could think of any thing that
would add to the elegance or beauty of the
furniture
,
she
need only mention her
wishes
to have them
complied with. She next
displayed
a variety of
elegant female apparel, toys, jewels, and other
things proper to catch the attention of
inexperienced
youth, and kindle the glowing
seeds
of
vanity into a flame that might
consume
her,
at that time was without a favorite, and from the
prepossession
he felt in his
