occasioned
to envelope your
mind---what, though I am an old man, I will
teach you to love me.
Oh! Sir, replied Maran, you have taught me
that already, there is nothing which I
should
think too hard to perform, to convince you of the
grateful affections of my heart. But I had hoped
this
sinking
fragile frame never would have
known pollution more.
The Major endeavoured to calm the
