her.
I had a father once, I had a lover too; but you
see
how it is with me now, I am poor, very
wretched, and I
sometimes
think not quite in my
right
senses
. I have a mother who lives
somewhere
here about, I have travelled a long way in
hopes to find her, but I know not how it is, I
have eat
so
little, and wept
so
much, I was
obliged to
sit
